Pro-Tasker — Project & Task Manager

A full-stack project manager application built with React + TypeScript, providing users with a clean, interactive way to manage their projects and tasks.

Pro-Tasker includes both frontend and backend code (this repo contains the frontend).

 Project Overview

Pro-Tasker allows users to:
 User Management
	• Create an account and log in.
	• Maintain a secure session.
	• Log out safely.
 Project Management
	• Create new projects with a name and description.
	• View a dashboard of all projects.
	• Open the details of a single project.
	• Update or delete only the projects they     own.
 Task Management
 Inside each project, users can:
	• Create tasks with a title, description, and status (To Do, In Progress, Done).
	• View all tasks belonging to a project.
	• Update task details or change their status.
	• Delete tasks from projects they own.

 What This Project Demonstrates
	• API integration (frontend + backend communication)
	• Global state management with Context API
	• Routing with React Router 
	• Clean, reusable component architecture
	• Responsive UI using Tailwind CSS
	• Authentication & protected routes

 Features
 Home Page
	• Friendly message
	• Buttons for Register/Login
	• Navigation to authentication pages
 Register Page
	• Account creation form (username, email, password)
	• Submit button + navigation to Login page
 Login Page
	• Email + password form
	• Sets user authentication state (see the context)
 Projects Dashboard
	• List of all user-owned projects
	• Button to add a new project
 Project Details Page
	• View project title & description
	• Update or delete project
	• Create tasks
	• View all associated tasks

 Tech Stack
Frontend
	• React + TypeScript
	• Vite (build tool)
	• Tailwind CSS (styling)
	• React Router (routing)
	• Context API (global state management)
	• Axios (API requests)
	• npm (package manager)

Backend (API used by this frontend)
This frontend interacts with endpoints for:
	1. Create a user
	2. Log in a user
	3. Create a project
	4. Get all projects
	5. Get a single project
	6. Update a project
	7. Delete a project
	8. Create a task
	9. Get all tasks
	10. Get a single task
	11. Update a task
	12. Delete a task

 Installation
git clone https://github.com/kbieman21/pro-tasker-frontend
cd pro-tasker-frontend
npm install

 Running Locally
npm run dev
Open the app in your browser:
 http://localhost:5173
 
 Deployment
Frontend (Netlify)
This frontend applicatio is deployed on Netlify and accessible here:
https://protasker-frontend.netlify.app

Backend (Render)
The frontend communicates with the backend API hosted on Render:
Backend API Base URL:
https://pro-tasker-backend-61bs.onrender.com
Make sure your .env contains:
VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://pro-tasker-backend-61bs.onrender.com


